\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator stated that the programme in terms of all the criteria to be assessed for a public institution meets the minimum requirements for accreditation and recommended that the programme should be accredited without conditions.  \line \line The programme is in line with the Institution\'27s mission. This programme also aims to address the scarce and critical skills of the financial sector in the country. The programme is coherently designed and meets the needs of students by providing Diplomates an opportunity to articulate onto a 1-year \'28128 credit\'29 NQF Level 7 qualification. Financial Accounting\'2C Management Account\'2C Auditing and Taxation are the core subject areas that will be covered in this programme. \line \line Vertical articulation will be possible into various NQF Level 8 programmes such as\'2C a Postgraduate Diploma or Honours programmes in Accounting\'2C Cost \'26 Management Accounting\'2C Auditing\'2C or Taxation or potentially a Postgraduate Diploma or Honours in Accounting Science of Certificate of Theory in Accounting \'28CTA Level 1\'29. This will be possible when the programme has been submitted to the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants \'28SAICA\'29. Following this\'2C articulation onto a Masters qualification will be possible. Horizontal articulation will be possible to other Advanced Diploma qualifications across public and private institutions.\line \line Student admission requirements include either\'2C an appropriate Diploma in Accounting or Cost and Management Accounting with an average pass mark from the big four subjects \'28Financial accounting\'2C Management accounting and finance\'2C Auditing and Taxation\'29 of at least 60\'25 in each of the final level 6 subjects. Where a student obtained less than 60\'25\'2C a minimum of two years Accounting work experience will be required. RPL candidates will be admitted in accordance with the RPL Policy. The envisaged enrollment will accommodate a maximum of 90 students \'2850 in day and 40 in the evening\'29. The evening classes will widen access by availing the programme to working adults. \line \line As this is a public Institution\'2C Criteria 3\'2C 4\'2C 7 and 8 are deemed to be in place.\line \line Teaching and learning has been described. A Policy around the Development and the Review of Learning Materials exists. This Policy includes broad principles around developing and reviewing learning materials as well as outlining the duties and responsibilities of the various academic staff members entrusted with learning materials development. The Institution has put in place various support mechanisms to provide social and academic support to ensure that students are work-ready. The Policy for addressing students at-risk revolves around the lecturer providing one-on-one support to students who are struggling with a particular course during consultation hours. Staff members within the department will provide subject specific interventions to assist students\'2C and use is also made of tutors\'2C mentors and peer helpers. Student progress will be monitored through class attendance\'2C class tests\'2C spot tests\'2C assignments\'2C presentations and all means of formative assessments. \line \line Formative and summative assessments will be conducted throughout the programme with planned continuous feedback provided to students. There will be three formative assessments in the form of 2-hour tests\'2C and any one of the following\'3B assignment\'2C case studies\'2C projects\'3B and one summative assessment comprising of a three-hour written examination. Online assessments are followed by immediate feedback. Timeous feedback is regarded as an integral part of formative assessments. \line \line External moderators will be suitably qualified and experienced members from industry and\'2For practicing academics from other universities. The procedure for the appointment of external moderators is laid down in the institutional examination\'27s manual. \line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited.\cell \pard 

